definition: surname Wei/ancient Chinese state near present day Chongqing/Taiwan pr. [Wei2]

sentences.english: Only for a laugh, and caught up in the humbler memories of the misery of it.
sentences.chinese: 只爲一個笑，而陶醉於那微賤的回念裏沒有成自拔。
但是他的出身卻是微賤的。

sentences.english: A woman of no birth may marry into the purple.
sentences.chinese: 出身微賤的姑娘會因結婚而貴。

sentences.english: "Had I been born in a royal family, " said the bastardly man.
sentences.chinese: “假若我出身於王室，”這個出身微賤的人說道。

sentences.english: The general rose from humble beginnings.
With humble, when two princes to east, the meteorite first can report.
sentences.chinese: 猥以微賤，當待東宮，非臣隕首所能上報。
